{
  "ref": "Psalms 112",
  "heRef": "תהילים קי״ב",
  "isComplex": false,
  "text": [
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\">Hallelujah.</span><br><span class=\"poetry indentAll\"> <b>א</b> Happy are those who fear G<small>OD</small>,</span><br><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">who are ardently devoted to God’s commandments.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>ג</b> Their descendants will be mighty in the land,</span><br><b>ד</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\"> a blessed generation of the upright.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>ה</b> Wealth and riches are in their house,</span><br><b>ו</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\"> and their beneficence lasts forever.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>ז</b> A light shines<sup class=\"footnote-marker\">a</sup><i class=\"footnote\"><b>A light shines </b>Or “[God] shines as a light.”</i> for the upright in the darkness;</span><br><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\"><sup class=\"footnote-marker\">b</sup><i class=\"footnote\"><b>they are </b>Or “[God] is.”</i> gracious, compassionate, and beneficent.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>ח</b> <b>ט</b> All goes well with those who lend generously,</span><br><b>י</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">who conduct affairs with equity.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>כ</b> They shall never be shaken;</span><br><b>ל</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">the beneficent will be remembered forever.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>מ</b> They are not afraid of evil tidings;</span><br><b>נ</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">their heart is firm, they trust in G<small>OD</small>.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>ס</b> Their heart is resolute, they are unafraid;</span><br><b>ע</b><span class=\"poetry indentAll\">in the end they will see the fall of their foes.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>פ</b> They give freely to the poor;</span><br><b>צ</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">their beneficence lasts forever;</span><br> <b>ק</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">their horn is exalted in honor.</span>",
    "<span class=\"poetry indentAll\"><b>ר</b> The wicked shall see it and be vexed;</span><br><b>ש</b><span class=\"poetry indentAllDouble\">they shall gnash their teeth; their courage shall fail.<br><b>ת</b><span class=\"poetry indentAll\">The desire of the wicked shall come to nothing.</span>"
  ],
  "he": [
    "הַ֥לְלוּ<span class=\"mam-implicit-maqaf\">־</span>יָ֨הּ&thinsp;<b>׀</b> אַשְׁרֵי־אִ֭ישׁ יָרֵ֣א אֶת־יְהֹוָ֑ה בְּ֝מִצְוֺתָ֗יו חָפֵ֥ץ מְאֹֽד׃",
    "גִּבּ֣וֹר בָּ֭אָרֶץ יִהְיֶ֣ה זַרְע֑וֹ דּ֖וֹר יְשָׁרִ֣ים יְבֹרָֽךְ׃",
    "הוֹן־וָעֹ֥שֶׁר בְּבֵית֑וֹ וְ֝צִדְקָת֗וֹ עֹמֶ֥דֶת לָעַֽד׃",
    "זָ֘רַ֤ח בַּחֹ֣שֶׁךְ א֭וֹר לַיְשָׁרִ֑ים חַנּ֖וּן וְרַח֣וּם וְצַדִּֽיק׃",
    "טֽוֹב־אִ֭ישׁ חוֹנֵ֣ן וּמַלְוֶ֑ה יְכַלְכֵּ֖ל דְּבָרָ֣יו בְּמִשְׁפָּֽט׃",
    "כִּֽי־לְעוֹלָ֥ם לֹֽא־יִמּ֑וֹט לְזֵ֥כֶר ע֝וֹלָ֗ם יִהְיֶ֥ה צַדִּֽיק׃",
    "מִשְּׁמוּעָ֣ה רָ֭עָה לֹ֣א יִירָ֑א נָכ֥וֹן לִ֝בּ֗וֹ בָּטֻ֥חַ בַּיהֹוָֽה׃",
    "סָמ֣וּךְ לִ֭בּוֹ לֹ֣א יִירָ֑א עַ֖ד אֲשֶׁר־יִרְאֶ֣ה בְצָרָֽיו׃",
    "פִּזַּ֤ר&thinsp;<b>׀</b> נָ֘תַ֤ן לָאֶבְיוֹנִ֗ים צִ֭דְקָתוֹ עֹמֶ֣דֶת לָעַ֑ד קַ֝רְנ֗וֹ תָּר֥וּם בְּכָבֽוֹד׃",
    "רָ֘שָׁ֤ע יִרְאֶ֨ה&thinsp;<b>׀</b> וְכָעָ֗ס שִׁנָּ֣יו יַחֲרֹ֣ק וְנָמָ֑ס תַּאֲוַ֖ת רְשָׁעִ֣ים תֹּאבֵֽד׃&nbsp;<span class=\"mam-spi-pe\">{פ}</span><br>"
  ],
